The goal of this test case is to check that localization support is functional during the installation from a live cd session and that language packs are downloaded and installed correctly from the Internet.
<!-- Smells: UNVERIFIED STEPS -->
Ensure the live session has started (1)
Ensure Ubiquity starts click on Forwar (2)
Ensure the installer has finished choose to Restart the system no (3)
<dl>
    <dt>Boot up the image</dt>
		<dd>[FILL VERIFICATION]</dd>
    <dt>Select a non-English language</dt>
	<dt>press Enter</dt>
	<dd>The boot screen is displayed in the selected language</dd>
    <dt>Select Try FAMILY without any change to your computer</dt>
	<dt>press Enter</dt>
        <dd>
            <ul>
                <li>verify that the system is localized to the previously selected language (1)</li>
            </ul>
        </dd>
    <dt>Double click on the Install icon</dt>
		<dd>[FILL VERIFICATION]</dd>
    <dt>nce Ubiquity starts click on Forward (2)</dt>
    <dt>Select the same non English language from the list</dt>
	<dt>click Forward</dt>
    <dt>Check your keyboard layout is correct</dt>
	<dt>alter click Forward</dt>
    <dt>Select Erase</dt>
	<dt>use the entire disk</dt>
	<dt>click Forward</dt>
    <dt>Select your timezone</dt>
	<dt>click Forward</dt>
    <dt>Input your initial user details</dt>
	<dt>password Note admin can not be used it is a dedicated Linux User</dt>
    <dt>Tick Log in automatically</dt>
	<dt>click on Forward</dt>
    <dt>Check the details are correct on the final page</dt>
	<dt>click Install</dt>
    <dt>nce the installer has finished choose to Restart the system now (3)</dt>
    <dt>Remove the disc</dt>
	<dt>press Enter</dt>
    <dt>Allow the machine to reboot</dt>
		<dd>[FILL VERIFICATION]</dd>
    	<dd>Verify that your system is localized:</dd>
        <dd>
            <ul>
                <li>For any language, the system has to be fully localized. Note: the translation coverage of some languages might not be complete</li>
            </ul>
        </dd>
    	<dd>Check that the calendar shows the regional settings correctly</dd>
		<dd>[FILL VERIFICATION]</dd>
</dl>
